cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also extensively experiments with different techniques to improve the accuracy and robustness of the model, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes a new model architecture, which could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the model on several open datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
